<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="512" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,221,463]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,365,391]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to the original illustrations (
<bibRefCitation author="Gravely, F. H." box="[771,932,365,391]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" pagination="211 - 282" refId="ref7267" refString="Gravely, F. H. (1931) Some Indian spiders of the families Ctenidae, Sparassidae, Selenopidae and Clubionidae. Records of the Indian Museum, Calcutta, 33, 211 - 282." type="journal article" year="1931">Gravely 1931</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 19J–K, herein 
<figureCitation box="[1160,1226,365,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1973,1997]" captionTargetBox="[358,1228,1366,1942]" captionTargetId="figure-570@6.[350,1238,1353,1950]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Sphingius bilineatus Simon, 1906. Original illustrations of Ƌ pedipalp (A) and ♀ genitalia (B) adopted from Gravely (1931). Figures not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4387687" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4387687/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
A–B), this species may be a senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gravely" authorityYear="1931" box="[482,646,401,427]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Sphingius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barkudensis">
<emphasis box="[482,646,401,427]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">S. barkudensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, confirmation requires examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[1250,1298,401,427]" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">type</typeStatus>
or topotype materials of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1906" box="[291,429,437,463]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Sphingius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilineatus">
<emphasis box="[291,429,437,463]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="512">S. bilineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
